_header: Sithen the first that were here or may be
Subjects: historical poems; Whitby Haven, naval battle of, 1451
_description: Description of the English naval victory over the French at Whitby Haven in 1451 — 120 lines in 8-line stanzas

TCD516.First Lines:
Sythen the furste þat were here or may beWretyn in brute
                    cronycle or yeste…
TCD516.Last Lines:
…And amende þe diuisioun in oure lordes partyAmen pray
                        we we all for charite
TCD516.Editions:
Robbins,  Rossell Hope. 
             “Victory at Whitby, A.D. 1451.” 
             Studies in Philology
         67 (1970): 495-504: 499.
